getting-started/INSTALLATION.html.body:
Installation
The module is available on npm.
To install it in your project, let's run:
$ npm install rn-placeholder --save

or
$ yarn add rn-placeholder

In your code
Import the module and display a placeholder inside your component:
import Placeholder from 'rn-placeholder';

/*...*/
render() {
    return (


          Placeholder has finished :D


    );
  }
/*...*/

The onReady props is available on every component. It manages the React element to display.
In this example, when the value of this.state.isReady will change to something existing, the  component will be rendered instead of the Placeholder.ImageContent.

